# Project: Nesso

Nesso is an AI-powered knowledge graph for active learning. Users build concept maps by placing nodes (ideas) and drawing typed semantic edges between them. A Socratic AI mentor probes their understanding through dialogue rather than explanation.

## Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Framework | React 18 + Vite + TypeScript |
| Graph canvas | React Flow (`@xyflow/react`) |
| State | Zustand (`src/store/graph.ts`) |
| AI mentor | Provider-agnostic chat API (currently `@anthropic-ai/sdk`, swappable) |

## Source layout

```
src/
  App.tsx             # Root: keyboard shortcuts, theme application, layout
  components/         # All UI components (see components.mdc)
  store/graph.ts      # Single Zustand store for all app state
  data/
    edgeTypes.ts      # EDGE_TYPES and EDGE_CATEGORIES — the semantic relation model
    palettes.ts       # CSS variable colour palettes for edge categories
    seedGraph.ts      # Initial demo graph + SOCRATIC_PROMPTS
  types/graph.ts      # ConceptNodeData, EdgeTypeName, NessoSettings, etc.
```

## Core concepts

- **Node** — a `ConceptNode` with `text`, `conf` (1–5), `reviewed` (days ago), `pinned`.
- **Edge** — a React Flow edge of type `'nesso'`, carrying `data.type: EdgeTypeName`.
- **Selection** — a single `{ kind: 'node' | 'edge', id }` tracked in the store. Drives the Inspector and Socrates opening prompt.
- **Settings** — `NessoSettings` in the store (dark mode, accent, encoding, palette, etc.). Applied via CSS custom properties on `<html>`.
